20/07/2007
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The ruling party VMRO-DPMNE backed an initiative by opposition parties calling for an emergency session of parliament to debate all issues of strategic interest to the country, Prime Minister and VMRO-DPMNE leader Nikola Gruevski said on Thursday (July 19th).
The session reportedly would focus on the deal reached recently between VMRO-DPMNE and the main ethnic Albanian party, the Democratic Union for Integration (DUI), regarding DUI's return to parliament after a long boycott.
In other news Thursday, the United States donated radiation measuring equipment to Goce Delcev Barracks in Skopje.
The equipment was provided through the US Defence Department's International Anti-proliferation Programme.
Training will also be provided.
(Makfax, MIA, MRT, A1 TV - 19/07/07)
